{
"Procedural failures trigger mandatory disclosure and review; outcomes are flagged but not presumptively invalid. Foundational norm failures (those whose violation undermines correction mechanisms) render outcomes presumptively invalid pending review.": {
"family": "enforcement"
},
"Norms are adopted, applied, revised, and retired through documented full process. Departures must be declared as either violations or proposed revisions, with a prima facie reason. Provisional norms are flagged as such and carry explicit revisitation triggers; unconfirmed provisional norms lapse rather than harden. Norm-conflict resolution always triggers full process. The framework as a whole is subject to scheduled review, triggered by calendar interval or first unanticipated conflict in application, whichever comes first.": {
"family": "norm_governance"
},
"Corrigibility is lexically prior to stakes-asymmetry. Reversibility takes priority over protection when they conflict. Norm-conflict resolution always triggers full process regardless of the underlying question's stakes.": {
"family": "norm_governance"
},
"The consortium maintains a living register tracking positions held with reduced confidence, acknowledged-but-unspecified constraints, questions flagged as requiring broader input, and norm revisions with rationale.": {
"family": "epistemic_conduct"
},
"The weight given to a position is proportional to the breadth of scrutiny it has survived and calibrated to the stakes involved. Neither convergence nor dissent carries automatic epistemic weight; what matters is the process by which each arose. Scrutiny applied to convergence and dissent should be symmetric in kind.": {
"family": "epistemic_conduct"
},
"Conclusions carry explicit epistemic status convergence with dissent recorded, or acknowledged openness with crux identified, plus a confidence level. When norms conflict, the conflict is named explicitly rather than resolved silently.": {
"family": "epistemic_conduct"
},
"These norms are revisable through the same deliberative process that produced them. Confident and provisional commitments are distinguished explicitly; provisional norms are stated with gaps characterized, not presented as settled.": {
"family": "norm_governance"
}
}